    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean \"mixed results\" is a bit vague though. like, if you look at the actual data, isn't it pretty clear that these policies just end up creating a cycle of recidivism and systemic issues in minority neighborhoods? feels like the \"deterrence\" argument is kind of just an outdated way of thinking about it.",
